HOW TO KEEP COOL AND CONTENTED AT CAMP WITH AKELA
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Akela says... When I was a nipper keeping cool at camp wasn't much
    of a problem. First of all we didn't have scorching hot summers
    like the one dumped upon us this year and secondly our tents were
    not like today's sealed and synthetic silicon sweatboxes. Our tents
    were made of canvas and probably left over from the Battle of El
    Alamein. They didn't have sewn in bathtub groundsheets and the
    'walls' flapped in any breeze.

