A CHILD'S MEMORY OF THE NHS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    When I was a child I lived in a flat in Lausanne Road in Hornsey,
    part of what is known now as the 'Haringey Ladder'. The area got
    this name as it consisted of a series of parallel streets, like the
    rungs on a ladder, bounded to east and west by Wightman Road and
    Green Lanes.

